<function>

access:   public

name: validate

param: array, $submit, NULL

return: bool

</function>

Performs filtering and validation on each form element.

* Parameters:

 * array //$submit//: The source data array for populating form values as array(name => info); if null, will populate from $_POST or $_GET as determined from the 'method' attribute.

* Returns bool: True if all elements are valid, false if not.

Updates the feedback keys for each element that fails validation.
Values are either pulled from the submitted form or from the array
passed in $submit.